cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on user behavior in Online Social Networks (OSNs), specifically on Facebook, and how users orchestrate the offered functions to achieve individual benefit. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computers and Society (cs.CY), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also evaluates user activity changes from 2009 till 2014, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves analyzing and understanding data over time. Finally, the paper contributes evidence to the discussion of Facebook being an aging network, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC).
